A vintage 1960s-style technical illustration of a vast network of interconnected brass and copper pneumatic tubes stretching across a stylized globe, with small cylindrical message capsules racing through the transparent tubes in multiple directions simultaneously. The tubes connect ornate Victorian-era server towers with spinning gears and clockwork mechanisms, each tower topped with a glowing amber beacon. The color palette features warm sepia tones, aged parchment yellows, and burnished bronze metallics. Steam wisps curl from junction points where multiple tubes converge. The perspective is slightly elevated, showing the intricate web of connections spanning continents rendered in an antique cartographic style with cross-hatching and fine line work typical of old engineering diagrams.
